no Mars]], [[Kristin Chenoweth]], [[Rita Moreno]], [[Amandla Stenberg]], [[Rachel Crow]], [[Pierce Gagnon]], and [[Natalie Morales (journalist)|Natalie Morales]]. The sequel follows Blu, Jewel and their three kids on a venture into the [[Amazon rainforest|Amazon]] where they try to live like real birds. Eventually, they find Jewel's long-lost father Eduardo, who is in hiding with a tribe of other [[Spix's macaw]]. At first everything seems perfect, but Blu is having trouble adapting to the wild. Eventually, they discover that the Amazon is under threat, and that Blu and Jewel's old nemesis, Nigel the cockatoo, is back for revenge.<ref name=\"Cast\">{{cite web|url=http://blueskystudios.com/blog/entry/official-rio2-casting-press-release/ |title=Twentieth Century Fox Animation Announces Rio 2 Casting |publisher=Blue Sky Studios |date=February 22, 2013 |accessdate=February 22, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"Variety\">\n{{cite news\n| url=https://www.variety.com/article/VR1118003473\n| title=Fox, Blue Sky drawn to 'Rio'\n| last=Siegel\n| first=Tatiana\n| date=May 11, 2009\n| work=Variety\n| access-date=January 20, 2010\n}}</ref>\n\n<!--<ref name=\"BlueSky\">\n{{cite press release\n| title=Blue Sky's next feature 'Rio' on its way in April 2011\n| work=Blue Sky Studios\n| date=May 14, 2009\n| url=http://blueskystudios.com/content/company-pressrelease.php?id=30\n| access-date=October 7, 2010\n}}</ref> -->\n\n<ref name=\"CinemaBlend\">\n{{cite web\n| url=https://www.cinemablend.com/new/Neil-Patrick-Harris-Takes-Anne-Hathaway-To-Rio-15351.html\n| title=Neil Patrick Harris Takes Anne Hathaway To Rio\n| last=Gomez\n| first=Tim\n| date=October 22, 2009\n| work=Cinema Blend\n| access-date=January 20, 2010\n}}</ref>\n\n<!--<ref name=\"Blastr\">\n{{cite news\n| url=http://blastr.com/2009/06/why-the-animated-rio-is-i.php\n| title=Why the animated Rio is Ice Age director Carlos Saldanha's dream project\n| last=Topel\n| first=Fred\n| date=June 8, 2009\n| 